What counts as "code" vs "content"?
===================================

Code (MIT):
  - Shell scripts and setup tooling
  - .claude/skills/ and .agents/skills/ (SKILL.md instruction files)
  - .obsidian/ configuration files
  - Any future JavaScript/Python automation

Content (CC BY 4.0):
  - README.md, QUICK_START.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, and all other documentation
  - 00_System/ rules and writing conventions
  - Card templates in 04_Knowledge/00_Cards/.templates/
  - Project templates in 03_Projects/.templates/
  - Framework documents in 04_Knowledge/Frameworks/
  - Example cards, example projects, example daily notes
  - 07_Bases/ base definitions (treated as content)

When in doubt, treat as content (CC BY 4.0).
